definition: void of expression, a cartridge containing an explosive charge but no bullet, to keep the opposing baseball team from winning
details:
adjective
- void of expression
= example: void of expression
= synonyms: vacuous
- (of a surface) not written or printed on
= example: (of a surface) not written or printed on
= synonyms: white
- not charged with a bullet
= example: not charged with a bullet
noun
- a cartridge containing an explosive charge but no bullet
= synonyms: dummy, blank shell
- a piece of material ready to be made into something
- a blank gap or missing part
= synonyms: lacuna
- a blank character used to separate successive words in writing or printing
= synonyms: space
verb
- to keep the opposing baseball team from winning
= example: to keep the opposing baseball team from winning
